[00:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hi. Welcome to SCAIL-2. Another exciting Wan-2.1&nbsp; model has just been released 2 days ago. I&nbsp;&nbsp; honestly am having a bit of a hard time keeping&nbsp; up. But I will not give up! So, let\'s see if this&nbsp;&nbsp; will be better than it\'s predecessor. Alright.&nbsp; A couple of things before we jump in. SCAIL-2&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is now officially baked directly into ComfyUI — no&nbsp; custom nodes needed like the previous version. As&nbsp;&nbsp; of version 0.24.1, released in June 2026, ComfyUI&nbsp; ships with native SCAIL-2 support out of the box,&nbsp;&nbsp; including the new SCAIL-2-Colored-Mask and&nbsp; Wan-SCAIL-To-Video nodes built right into core.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is a big deal — just a while ago, SCAIL-1&nbsp; required the Wan-Video-Wrapper custom node,&nbsp;&nbsp; and SCAIL-2 was so new it only existed in KiJai\'s&nbsp; dev branch. Now all you need is a comfy update to&nbsp;&nbsp; get started. To be honest, as you saw in the&nbsp; samples, I think SCAIL-2 is really amazing and&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the output is totally different from SCAIL-1. This workflow is a test workflow made by KiJai&nbsp;&nbsp; himself. I have modified a bit to suit my own&nbsp; needs, and to meet some of my PC limitations,&nbsp;&nbsp; especially the 12 GB card PC. You may find it very&nbsp; different from the original one, so please bear in&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mind that this is not the official workflow. But I&nbsp; guarantee it runs on a 12 gigabyte VRAM GPU. Here&nbsp;&nbsp; are the models and direct links. Click to download&nbsp; and place them inside the folders listed here.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then we load our models here. I have also included&nbsp; the GGUF loader, but was not able to find any yet.&nbsp;&nbsp; So, keep an eye out. Now to the most important&nbsp; part, I think. The reference image and video,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'including audio. When we load our image to use&nbsp; as reference, if the aspect ratios of the image&nbsp;&nbsp; and the video aren\'t close enough, you may get a&nbsp; bad video, either the top or bottom of the image&nbsp;&nbsp; will be missing. So, I have added the resize node&nbsp; here to crop the part of the image that I need to&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stay in the frame of the generated video. For&nbsp; example, if this image is a portrait, and if&nbsp;&nbsp; my driving video is a landscape, I should crop the&nbsp; face part of the image so it will not be recreated&nbsp;&nbsp; by the model. I can either crop it at the top,&nbsp; bottom, center, and left or right. So, make sure&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you check the settings before running the flow.&nbsp; Then, we load out driving video here with some&nbsp;&nbsp; settings to keep in mind as well. Here we set the&nbsp; output video resolution and FPS. I have hooked the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'output video resolution and FPS into this node, so&nbsp; there is no need to re-enter the values elsewhere.&nbsp;&nbsp; You might need to do a bit calculation as well. I&nbsp; find 20 FPS is good enough, so I set it to 20. And&nbsp;&nbsp; I will need to recalculate the length accordingly.&nbsp; My original video is 241 frames long at 30 FPS,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that makes it an 8 seconds long video. But since&nbsp; I want a 5 second video at 20 FPS, I will need to&nbsp;&nbsp; set the total frame length to 101 frames. Also&nbsp; my video has an audio stream, so I added this&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'function here to switch audio on or off, true for&nbsp; on and false for off. Here we do the segmentation&nbsp;&nbsp; of both the image and video. We use SAM-3.1 which&nbsp; is the latest segment anything from Meta. Load the&nbsp;&nbsp; model here and write a short instruction prompt&nbsp; for what to segment here. Down here we enter&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'our main prompt. Then, here is the base generation&nbsp; group... and the group for frame interpolation and&nbsp;&nbsp; RTX upscaling. Change the VFI multiplier as needed&nbsp; and FPS will be calculated accordingly. Set the&nbsp;&nbsp; upscale factor and quality as per your liking. Okay... I have marked the important user settings&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in red. As you can see, there are 6 nodes&nbsp; that need user attention for every single run.&nbsp;&nbsp; Before I test run the workflow, I will need to&nbsp; double-check these settings first. Crop position,&nbsp;&nbsp; center... checked. Resolution, and FPS at 20...&nbsp; checked. I find that it works really well even at&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these low resolutions for a draft preview, with&nbsp; some added VFI and upscaling. Okay. Audio, on...&nbsp;&nbsp; checked. SAM\'s instructions, segment the person...&nbsp; checked. My prompt... checked. And finally,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the video length of 101 frames... checked. Ready&nbsp; to test run the workflow. So, the output video&nbsp;&nbsp; looks great, and I really like it. 201 frames&nbsp; at 40 FPS. Whatever that "Trans-of-R-ley" is...&nbsp;&nbsp;'

